---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Layout title="About | persistence" description="Professional accountability journal, profile, and personal growth principles.">
	<section class="about-view">
		<!-- Left: Text Column -->
		<div class="about-text-column">
			<header class="about-header">
				<span>Portfolio Context</span>
				<h1>About Me</h1>
			</header>
			
			<div class="about-content">
				<p>
					I am Kazuki Aoyama, and this is my accountability journal. My goal in life is to improve 1% every single day. Here is where I document the why and how of my growth, and maybe you can pick something up along the way.
				</p>
				
				<p class="principles-intro">
					The principles I will employ when creating posts are the following:
				</p>

				<ol class="principles-list">
					<li>
						<strong>High-Fidelity Data & Code:</strong> 
						Every code snippet must compile, calculations must resolve, and claims must hold mathematical weight. No hand-waving, generalizations, or shortcuts.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Uncompromising Honesty:</strong> 
						Like Marcus Aurelius’s <em>Meditations</em>, these notes are written to my own mind first. Performative complexity is stripped out—only raw, unvarnished truth.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Feynman-Style Teaching:</strong> 
						Teaching is my ultimate mental exercise. If I cannot explain a high-dimensional concept or system optimization pattern in clear, minimal terms, I do not truly understand it.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Systematic Inversion:</strong> 
						Inspired by Charlie Munger, I will document not just how ideas succeed, but how they break. "Invert, always invert" to avoid intellectual mistakes and prevent system degradation.
					</li>
				</ol>

				<hr class="section-divider" />

				<h2 class="sub-heading">Professional Connections</h2>
				<ul class="connections-list">
					<li>
						<strong>GitHub</strong> 
						<a href="https://github.com/aoyama-hub" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@aoyama-hub</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>LinkedIn</strong> 
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kazuki-aoyama/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Kazuki Aoyama</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Email Inquiry</strong> 
						<a href="mailto:k41aokazu1029@gmail.com">k41aokazu1029@gmail.com</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Right: Image Column -->
		<div class="about-image-column">
			<div class="profile-frame">
				<img 
					src={`${base}/profile.jpg`} 
					alt="Kazuki Aoyama" 
					class="profile-image"
				/>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	/* Split Grid Alignment */
	.about-view {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1.25fr 0.75fr;
		gap: 4.5rem;
		align-items: start;
		width: 100%;
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.about-view {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2.5rem;
		}
		.about-image-column {
			order: -1; /* Pulls profile picture to top on mobile views */
			max-width: 320px;
			margin: 0 auto;
		}
	}

	/* Text Styling Layout */
	.about-header {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	.about-header span {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 700;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 2.75rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0;
	}
	.about-content p {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: var(--text);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	/* Clean, professional principles list styling */
	.principles-intro {
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--text);
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	.principles-list {
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		margin: 0 0 2.5rem 0;
	}
	.principles-list li {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
		color: var(--text);
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
		padding-left: 0.5rem;
	}
	.principles-list strong {
		color: var(--accent);
		display: inline;
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
		margin-right: 0.25rem;
	}

	.section-divider {
		border: 0;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
		margin: 2.5rem 0;
	}
	.sub-heading {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 1rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		color: var(--muted);
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}
	.connections-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.connections-list li {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border);
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
	.connections-list strong {
		color: var(--text);
	}
	.connections-list a {
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 500;
	}
	.connections-list a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	/* Image Framing and Floating Sticky Mechanics */
	.profile-frame {
		border-radius: 16px;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		box-shadow: 0 12px 36px rgba(23, 40, 36, 0.08);
		overflow: hidden;
		width: 100%;
		aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
		background-color: var(--code-bg);
		position: sticky;
		top: 2rem; /* Keep image floating in frame as readers navigate your rules */
	}

	.profile-image {
		width: 100%;
		height: 100%;
		object-fit: cover;
		margin: 0 !important;
		border-radius: 0 !important;
		border: none !important;
	}
</style>